value.name: Centennial Correctional Facility - Colorado State Prisons
value.snippet: The Centennial Correctional Facility (CCF) in Cañon City, Colorado, opened its doors in 1980 as the state’s first maximum security prison. Initially serving this role until 1993, it was reclassified as a Level V maximum security facility in 2010, reflecting its commitment to housing high-custody offenders under strict security measures.
